EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL OFFENSES -- WEAPONS
***
1 This act would permit the possession or use of a muffler, silencer or other device on any
2 firearm longer than seventeen inches (17”) in length and would permit the use of such a device by
3 any person while hunting provided that they have a valid hunting license at the time of use. No
4 other city or state agency may enact any rule or regulation of law affecting the right to use such a
5 device.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
